def: One of a class of compounds formed from certain polybasicalcohols (and especially glycerin) by the substitution of chlorinefor one or more hydroxyl groups.
One who, or that which, upholds or sustains; a sustainer.[Obs.]I waked again, for my sustain was the Lord. Milton.
A keeper or feeder of sheep; also, an owner of sheep. 2 Kingsiii. 4.

Any one of several plants, as Artemisia santonica, andChenopodium anthelminticum, whose seeds have the property ofexpelling worms from the stomach and intestines. Wormseed mustard, aslender, cruciferous plant (Erysinum cheiranthoides) having smalllanceolate leaves.
The same, or equal, in law or right; one in kind or origin;analogous; similar. Dana.
